  "text": "Sintos and Tsaparas [CITATION_1] address the problem of inferring the strength of social ties (i.e., labeling the links of a given network as strong or weak) by leveraging the property in an elegant manner. They rst assume that users are more interested in establishing and maintaining strong ties, as presumably, this is the reason that they joined the network. Using this assumption they formulate the link-strength inference problem by asking to assign the maximal number of strong ties (or the minimal number of weak ties) so that the property holds. They prove that the problem is NP-hard and they devise an approximation algorithm for the variant of minimizing the number of weak ties.",
